{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> καρτερ-έω</b>, <br /> <b>to be steadfast, patient</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 1274, 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Σαμία” 112, etc.; ῥᾷον παραινεῖν ἢ παθόντα καρτερεῖν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 1078, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.64; κ. μάχῃ 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 837; κ. ἐλπίδι τινός 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.44: frequently with a _preposition_, κ. πρός τι\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>to hold up</b> against a thing, e.g. πρὸς ἡδονάς τε καὶ λύπας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 556c; πρὸς λιμὸν καὶ ῥῖγος 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 2.3.13; ἐπὶ τοῖς παροῦσι 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 6.48, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Laches” 194a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κ. ἐν ταῖς ἡδοναῖς <b>to be patient</b> or <b>temperate</b> in.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Lg.” 635c; ἐν πολέμῳ [prev. author] “La.” 193a \">Refs</a>]; κ. ἀπὸ τοῦ ὕπνου <b>refrain</b> therefrom, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “De Natura Animalium - Ar.Byzantine Epit.” 13.13 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: with <i>participle</i>, <b>persevere in</b> doing, οἱ δ᾽ ἐκαρτέρουν πρὸς κῦμα λακτίζοντες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 1395; κ. ἀναλίσκων ἀργύριον φρονίμως 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Laches” 192e; ἀκούων 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 3.241; κ. ἐν ἐπιτηδεύμασιν 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 2.32 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also τὰ δείν᾽ ἐκαρτέρουν <b>was</b> strangely <b>obdurate</b> or <b>obstinate</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 650 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: in later Prose meaning little more than <b>wait</b>, καρτέρει καὶ θεώρει <b>wait</b> and see, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.2Mac.7.17; οὐ κ. μέχρι θαλάμων ἐλθεῖν 2nd c.AD: Sextus Empiricus Philosophus “adversus Mathematicos” 1.291. \">LXX+2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> with <i>accusative</i> <i>of things</i>, <b>bear patiently, endure</b>, τὰ δ᾽ ἀδύναθ᾽ ἡμῖν καρτερεῖν οὐ ῥᾴδιον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 1370; κ. θεοῦ δόσιν [prev. author] Alcaeus1071; τῷ σώματι τὰ συντυγχάνοντα 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 1.6.7; τὸν τῶν ὑπεροπτικῶν ὄγκον 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 1.30; πολλὴν κακοπάθειαν 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1278b27:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, κεκαρτέρηται τἀμά my <b>time for patience is over</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 1457.--In 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus, οὐ καρτεριάδδει· οὐ φρόνιμος εἶ, should probably be οὐ καρτερίδδει (_Laconian dialect_ for καρτερίζει). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2594","accentedUnicode":"καρτερέω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2904","matchingForm":"κράτος","stepTransliteration":"kratos","gloss":"power","_zh_tw_Gloss":"權能","_es_Gloss":"poder","_zh_Gloss":"权能"}],"shortDef":"to persevere, endure","mediumDef":"to persevere, endure <br /><b>to be stout; to endure patiently, persevere, bear up with fortitude,</b> <ref='Heb.11.27'>Heb. 11:27</ref>*","stepGloss":"to endure","stepTransliteration":"kartereō","count":1,"_es_Definition":"permanecer firme, perseverar","_zh_tw_Definition":"忠貞不移 (來 11:27)","_zh_Definition":"忠贞不移 (来 11:27)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"đứng vững vàng; kiên trì","_zh_tw_Gloss":"恆心忍耐","_es_Gloss":"soportar","_zh_Gloss":"恒心忍耐"}]}